NPM:
    npm init -y     -->
        Auto-builds package.json

    npm install     -->
        Will install all missing dependencies found in
        package.json

    npm install {package name} -s   -->
        Install {package name} and save (-s) it as a
        dependency to the package.json

    npm list [-d {0-n}]     -->
        Lists all dependencies of current project
            -d depth flag allows to view at certain levels

    npm start       -->
        Create a "start" script in package.json, this 
        command will run the application give the value
        is the command that lanches the app
    


